opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph
Class LFGraphFactory

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.hylo.graph.LFGraphFactory

public class LFGraphFactory
extends Object

Factory class for creating LF graphs based on LFs and XML elements that represent them. Graph factories cannot be instantiated, however, their methods for building LF graphs are statically accessible.

Author:
Scott Martin
See Also:

newGraphFrom

public static LFGraph newGraphFrom(LF lf)
Creates a new LF graph based on the specified LF object. The LF object is first flattened, and then its LF ancestry structure is obtained by calling Flattener.getHighestParentMap().

This method makes two passes over the list of SatOps obtained by flattening the specified LF. The first pass adds vertices to the graph for every lexical predication, as determined by calling HyloHelper.isLexPred(LF) on the SatOp's nominal and proposition argument.

The second pass proceeds by cases, depending on the nature of the SatOp in question:

Lexical predications
cause the new LF graph to be updated with the corresponding LF ancestry, as determined by Flattener.getHighestParentMap().
Relation predications
cause a new LFEdge to be added to the LF graph based on the SatOp's argument and the argument's mode.
Attribute-value predications
cause the vertex corresponding to the SatOp's nominal to have attributes added based on the SatOp's argument.
where the nature of the SatOp in question is determined using HyloHelper.isLexPred(LF), HyloHelper.isRelPred(LF), and HyloHelper.isAttrPred(LF).

Parameters:
lf - The LF object to build an LF graph for.
Returns:
A new LF graph whose vertices represent the nominals in the LF's flattened representation and whose edges represent its relation predications.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - If lf is null.
